{"lemma":"شَهادَةٍ","slug":"شَهادَةٍ","root":"ش.ه.د","root_slug":"ش-ه-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ه-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَهادَة","root":"شهد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":26},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23194"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَهِدَ (šahida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"testimony, witness","examples":[{"text":"وَٱلَّذِينَ يَرْمُونَ ٱلْمُحْصَنَاتِ ثُمَّ لَمْ يَأْتُوا بِأَرْبَعَةِ شُهَدَاءَ فَٱجْلِدُوهُمْ ثَمَانِينَ جَلْدَةً وَلَا تَقْبَلُوا لَهُمْ شَهَادَةً أَبَدًا وَأُولَٰئِكَ هُمُ ٱلْفَاسِقُونَ","english":"As for those who accuse chaste women and do not bring four witnesses, strike them eighty lashes, and never accept any testimony from them after that, and they are transgressors."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"statement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"certificate, certification, testimonial, affidavit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diploma"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"transcript"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attestation, attest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"credentials, identification"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creed; credo"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shahada: the basic Islamic creed, or one of its two parts, i.e. faith in one God and in Muhammad as his prophet; collectively also called الشَّهَادَتَانِ (aš-šahādatāni)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"martyrdom"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃa.haː.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23194","headword_ar":"شَهَادَةٌ","root":"$hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Information of what one has witnessed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beheld with his eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Mgh, L, Msb:) this is the primary signification: (L:) said to be a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$aAhadapu","text_ar":"المُشَاهَدَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declaration of what one knows: testimony, attestation, evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"witness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decisive information."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oath:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahaAdaAtN","text_ar":"شَهَادَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the Kur xxiv. 6 [and 8]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Martyrdom in the cause of God's religion."},{"kind":"page_break","n":1611},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahiydN","text_ar":"شَهِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$ohadN","text_ar":"مَشْهَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. below: see the latter word. ―         -b5-  [And it is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aAhadN","text_ar":"مُشَاهَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimu Algayobi waAl$~ahaAdapi","text_ar":"عَالِمُ الغَيْبِ وَالشَّهَادَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur vi. 73 &c., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Knower of what is unseen and of what is seen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.)"}],"source_refs":["IF","Mgh","L","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}